Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.00,0:00:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,｢There was a hungry crow｣
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.00,0:00:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,｢who wanted to get some feed｣
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.00,0:00:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,｢If only this beak were longer｣
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.00,0:00:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,｢That feed would be a bit closer.｣
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.00,0:01:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,｢a crow can think｣
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.00,0:01:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,｢can think... can think｣
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.00,0:01:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Observe, propose a hypothesis, experiment and consider results.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.00,0:01:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Learn the way of scientific thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.67,0:01:31.87,white-large,,0,0,0,,{\pos(391.2,126.8)}Thinking\NObservation
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.00,0:01:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We begin with a ｢Thinking Observation｣.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.00,0:01:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If we make a loop out of paper, and cut through the middle with scissors...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.00,0:01:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It becomes two rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.00,0:01:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Today we will be observing this.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.00,0:01:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This time we give it a half turn before attaching it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.00,0:02:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we cut right down the middle with a pair of scissors...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.00,0:02:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's twisted but it becomes one big loop.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.00,0:02:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, after an initial half turn, we give it one further half turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.00,0:02:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In total it's turned one full time. Let's try cutting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.00,0:02:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It became two rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.00,0:02:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They're connected, but it's two.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.00,0:02:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did the ring sometimes become one ring and sometimes two?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.88,0:02:57.56,white-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(134.4,254.8)}(not twisted)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.88,0:02:57.56,white-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(408,247.6)}(one twist)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.88,0:02:57.56,white-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(275.2,247.2)}(half twist)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.00,0:03:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's try observing with color applied to both edges of the strip.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.00,0:03:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When we give it a half twist, it's connected like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.00,0:03:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If we traverse from here, red connects to blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.00,0:03:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And going around, it's connected to back to red.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.00,0:03:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We return to our inital position.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.00,0:03:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it that the red and blue lines at the strip's edge
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.00,0:03:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,are connected as one?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.00,0:03:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And thus...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.00,0:03:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it becomes one single loop?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.00,0:03:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what happened when we gave it a full turn?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.00,0:04:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Connecting red to red,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.00,0:04:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and connecting blue to blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.00,0:04:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If we cut this...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.00,0:04:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It becomes two loops, red and blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.00,0:04:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what will happen in this case?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.00,0:04:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We draw three lines and connect a loop with a half turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.00,0:04:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If we cut the white part in the space between the lines
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.00,0:04:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How many rings will will there be?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.00,0:04:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If we look at the place they join, first red to yellow...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.00,0:05:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,then yellow to red.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.00,0:05:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Blue is only connected to blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.00,0:05:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What will happen?
